childComplete

public void childComplete(IAeBpelObject aChild)
                   throws AeBusinessProcessException
Callback method that indicates a child object has completed. It is important to note that the child's state will be either FINISHED or DEAD_PATH.

Parameters:
aChild - The child completing its execution.
Throws:
AeBusinessProcessException

childTerminated

public void childTerminated(IAeBpelObject aChild)

public void childCompleteWithFault(IAeBpelObject aChild,
                                   IAeFault aFaultObject)
                            throws AeBusinessProcessException
All implementation must be able to accept execution notifications from its children. Note if an implementation has no children it can have a stub method here.

aFaultObject - the chidl is completing with a fault.

childIsFaulting

public void childIsFaulting(IAeBpelObject aChild,
                            IAeFault aFaultObject)
Notification to parent that a child is faulting. This exists to give the parent a chance to record the fault in the event that there is another fault raised due to the link processing.
